  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihoods Support for Afghan Refugees and Host Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Provision of marketable skills in different trades;
- Provision of add-on numeracy and literacy classes to illiterate beneficiaries to facilitate trainees&#x2019; learning and progress; 
- Job placement;
- Provision of training on small enterprise development; 
- Provision of cash grants;
- Provision of tool kits;
- Follow-up and monitoring of trainees after they have been placed or have started their own business.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghan refugees and host communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to increase access to employment and targets both Afghan refugees and host communities in Pakistan. Access to employment is facilitated through a multipronged approach including vocational training, small enterprise development support, provision of tool kits, provision of mini-grants and linkages with employers.</narrative>
  </description>
